Red Wings Defeat Coyotes 4-3 to Take 2-0 Lead in NHL Playoff Series

-- B y   B o b   B e n s c h
-- 
2011-04-16T20:05:06Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-16/red-wings-defeat-coyotes-4-3-to-take-2-0-lead-in-nhl-playoff-series.html
The Detroit  Red Wings  held on to
defeat the Phoenix Coyotes 4-3 and take a two-games-to-none lead
in their National Hockey League playoff series.  Pavel Datsyuk had a goal and three assists to lead the Red
Wings at Joe Louis Arena in Detroit. Brian Rafalski, Darren Helm
and Tomas Holmstrom also scored for Detroit, which led 4-0 in
the second period.  Shane Doan scored two goals for Phoenix, which hosts Game 3
of the best-of-seven Western Conference series in two days.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Bob Bensch at 
 bbensch@bloomberg.net  